{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:31:24.353Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Client Data Structure**\n\nOkay, so I've now got a solid handle on the `ClientAccount` structure. It looks like we have key fields such as `id`, `name`, `domain`, and status. I'm also examining the remaining data points like `tier`, `createdAt`, region, complianceLevel, and the contact details to see how they interplay.\n\n\n**Defining Client Management Scope**\n\nOkay, the `/admin/clients` internal management page is the focus now, and I'm parsing the requirements. I've defined the key fields for the client list/table: search, status filters, region filters, industry filters, account owner, active project count, and AI operations count. I'm taking care to scope the work, focusing on a polished UI with a representative client preview, no backend, and specific frontend actions. I am avoiding the landing page.\n\n\n**Extending Client Data Model**\n\nOkay, so I realized I need to enhance the client data model for this view. While the base `ClientAccount` doesn't include billing or health status, I think defining an extended type for the `/admin/clients` preview is the right approach. I'm focusing on adding `billingStatus` and `healthStatus`, as well as potentially `accountOwner`, `activeProjectsCount`, and `aiOpsCount`. I'm going to look into extending the client object type now to include this.\n\n\n**Evaluating Data Table Integration**\n\nI'm now integrating the data model with the `DataTable` component to understand rendering. I'm taking the structure of `DataTable` columns, data, and detail render into account. I'm considering how to best handle the new properties (like billing status and health status) in the frontend rendering of the table rows and detail views. I'm focusing on the component's existing API to extend functionality and enrich the data as needed, or utilize a custom interface like `AdminClientExtended` in this context. I need to make sure the data is readily available for the detail drawer.\n\n\n"}}
