{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:31:40.346Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering Admin Client Needs**\n\nI'm now focusing on the `/admin/clients` page. It's become clear that its filtering and field requirements differ significantly from the simpler `previewClientAccounts` array. I need to enumerate the necessary features for this particular admin section, especially since it needs to allow filtering on Status, Region, and Industry, as well as include fields beyond the basic preview data. The list is beginning.\n\n\n**Designing Enhanced Client View**\n\nNow, I'm envisioning a significantly improved `/admin/clients` page. It seems a custom, senior-designer worthy page is key. I'm focusing on incorporating metric boxes for summary stats, a rich search and filter section using inputs, dropdowns/pills, and a highly polished table. This refined table would showcase key columns like Client Name, Industry, Region, Account Owner, active project count, AI operations count, billing and health status, and status. I'm looking at potential actions for each table row.\n\n\n**Envisioning Client Portal Access**\n\nI'm now thinking about allowing admins to \"View Portal Preview\". I can let them set the active user/role, open a preview portal view modal, or navigate to `/portal/dashboard` using the client's context. I also want to incorporate \"Assign Owner\" functionality, as a dialog to change the owner, and \"Client Details\" to open a detail drawer. I also have an \"Add Client Preview\" modal in mind.\n\n\n**Defining Admin Control Center**\n\nI'm now establishing the core design for the `/admin/clients` page. It's envisioned as a command center for AI administrators, the \"sovereign control board\" for overseeing corporate tenants, sandboxes, and compliance. The design concept focuses on a dark, premium aesthetic with a \"sovereign control center\" visual metaphor, incorporating glowing state indicators, sharp borders, and an enterprise glassmorphism feel, consistent with an enterprise AI design system. The page is intended to be a hub to quickly see client health, regional load, owner assignment, and client workspace previews.\n\n\n**Refining Interface Elements**\n\nI'm now focusing on specific interface components for the `/admin/clients` page. I'm prioritizing a sophisticated filter and search bar with dropdowns for region, industry, and status, a search input, and a secondary-accented \"Add Client\" button. The data grid will be an elegant enterprise table with visual hierarchy, badge indicators, and action buttons. I envision a detail drawer for in-depth client information and lightweight modals for adding clients and assigning owners. Micro-animations and live state updates will enhance the interactive experience.\n\n\n"}}
