{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:31:50.701Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Component Structure**\n\nI've made good progress! I've confirmed the elegant structure of `WorkspaceCard`, `MetricTile`, and `StatusBadge` within `components/private-app/cards-metrics-badges.tsx`. Now, I'm exploring the exports from `@/components/private-app` to optimize importing strategies, aiming for streamlined component usage.\n\n\n**Matching Task Requirements**\n\nI'm now meticulously matching the task requirements. I've broken down the client list into fields, considering search, filters (status, region, industry, account owner), and counts (active projects, AI operations). I'm populating missing data for mock clients from `lib/mock-data-model.ts`, such as adding an `industry` field for each client for proper testing. I'm focusing on local page state to augment the data.\n\n\n**Defining Client Parameters**\n\nI'm now defining the structure of the client data. I've populated the fields `accountOwner`, `activeProjectsCount`, `aiOpsCount`, `billingStatus`, and `healthStatus` for each client. I've also noted potential values for these fields, such as \"Paid\" or \"Active Plan\" for `billingStatus`. I'm starting to think about the required filters as well, such as \"Active,\" \"Suspended,\" and \"Pending\" for status, and regions like \"EU-West\" and \"US-East\".\n\n\n**Designing Client Interactions**\n\nI'm now designing the user interaction. I've focused on creating a detailed, local slide-out drawer for client information, keeping it secure and frontend-only. I've outlined key details to display within the drawer, including client name, owner info, system parameters, and dynamic lists of projects and AI operations. I'll dynamically populate the drawer with data from `previewProjects`, focusing on filtering by `clientAccountId`.\n\n\n**Implementing Agent Previews**\n\nI'm now implementing agent previews! I'm creating the billing preview, health telemetry, and rich action logs. I plan to incorporate data from `previewAgentOperations` by filtering based on project IDs from `previewProjects`. I am focused on displaying epoch metrics, latest invoice samples, uptime, latency simulation, CPU graphs, and the associated rich action logs.\n\n**Drafting Preview Actions**\n\nI'm carefully drafting frontend-only actions. I'm focusing on the \"Add Client Preview\" action. I've designed a \"+ Provision Client Account\" button that triggers a premium modal, which will include fields for enterprise name, domain namespace, industry selection, enclave region, subscription tier, account owner, health status, and billing status, to be added to the local react state upon submission.\n\n\n"}}
