 not found.\n\n\nI'm now designing the tabbed layout for the client detail drawer, which will be styled with horizontal monospace buttons. The active state indicators will create a high-tech modern interface.  I'm building out a cool, new \"Agents\" tab to render active agent operations, and show thread counts, memory allocations, and a simulated real-time telemetry log block. The last tab I'm building is for Billing to show subscription plan tier, compute credits, and ledger verification hash.\n\n\nI'm now implementing the client creation feature within the admin portal! I am incorporating input fields for domain, owner, health, and billing status, along with default values for contact details. Upon form submission, a new client object is generated and added to the client list state, complete with a system-provisioned contact and a notification banner, using a cool message! This process ensures a robust and informative experience.\n\n\nI'm now implementing the portal preview handshake modal! I am creating a simulated cryptographic handshake with a realistic progress bar. This modal will feature the client's name and domain, along with the security rule ISO-27001-A.9.2. A button will initiate the session, updating the local storage. This simulates a secure administrative mirroring session for a truly sovereign control experience!\n\n\nOkay, now I'm shifting focus to validating the code for `/app/admin/clients/page.tsx`! I need to ensure there are no compilation errors, layout issues, or Next.js route conflicts. I will carefully examine this file, replacing existing content, and then run build and linting commands to confirm its integrity. My goal is flawless deployment and a great user experience.\n\n\nI'm now focusing on verifying the `lucide-react` icon imports to ensure validity and support. I've confirmed all used icons (`Search`, `Plus`, `UserCheck`, etc.) are indeed valid and supported within the `lucide-react` library. This is critical for the UI design phase