{"ts":"2026-06-27T05:36:28.726Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"g82bnkw9","input":{"summary":"1. Design Narrative and Layout Strategy:\n   We built '/admin/clients' as the 'Sovereign Tenant Registry' dashboard. It is styled consistently with GFF AI's dark-mode, premium, high-contrast, Apple-like enterprise aesthetic. At the top of the workspace, a four-column live telemetry metric grid monitors managed enclaves, overall health SLA level, sandbox layers, and attestation credit spends.\n\n2. Fully Functional Search & Multi-Filters:\n   We integrated a sophisticated filter bar supporting real-time text-based search queries (matching on name, namespace, industry, owner, region, and ID) along with custom dropdown filters for status, enclave region, and industry sector.\n\n3. Complete Interactive Client List:\n   The table dynamically links to GFF AI's centralized mock data models ('previewProjects' and 'previewAgentOperations') to compute active projects count and live agent workloads for each corporate tenant. It includes beautiful, animated, and stateful badges for health (Healthy, Warning, Critical, Offline) and billing preview (Paid, Unpaid, Processing, Overdue).\n\n4. Advanced Tabbed Detail Drawer:\n   An elegant right-slide-out panel launches upon clicking any row, featuring a tabbed system:\n   - 'Overview': Displays custodian, tier, created epoch, active compliance standard, administrator contact, and a cryptographic Root Attestation certificate seal block.\n   - 'Projects': Dynamically renders cards for active sandbox enclaves belonging to the client (pulling from 'previewProjects').\n   - 'Agents': Displays live multi-agent runs, threading cores, memory utilization, and an eBPF log block.\n   - 'Billing': Outlines monthly credit rate limits and epoch ledger invoices.\n\n5. Premium Frontend-Only Actions (No Backend):\n   - 'Provision Tenant Account Modal': Opens a polished modal form that lets admins configure a new client. Submitting appends the new tenant to the local React state, making it immediately visible in the table and filters.\n   - 'Assign Account Custodian Modal': Provides an intuitive dropdown interface to change account owners, instantly updating the local state, table view, and details drawer.\n   - 'View Portal Preview Handshake': Triggers a multi-stage loading animation simulating a TLS 1.3 dual-layer cryptographic handshake before setting the client administrator session in 'localStorage' and routing them smoothly to '/portal/dashboard' for an immersive mirror experience.\n\n6. Validation and Linting Check:\n   We ran a targeted ESLint verification on the modified file, passing perfectly with zero errors or warnings. All rules and code continuity have been meticulously observed.","verified":true}}}
